-- Allstate Directors Smith, Farrell Step Down From Insurer’s Board
-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   B u n n
-- 2013-02-20T16:10:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-20/allstate-directors-smith-farrell-step-down-from-insurer-s-board.html
Allstate Corp., the largest publicly
traded U.S. home and auto insurer, said Joshua Smith and  James Farrell  will step down from the company’s board of directors.  Smith, 71, is reaching the retirement age set by Allstate’s
board policy, and Farrell, 70, will not seek re-election in May
for personal reasons, the Northbrook, Illinois-based company
said in a statement today distributed by PR Newswire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elizabeth Bunn in New York at 
